# SeaTrack Architecture

Expo SDK 55 · React 19 · React Native 0.83 · Expo Router · TypeScript (strict) · Firebase · TanStack Query.

## Layered folder structure (`src/`)

```
src/
  app/        # Expo Router routes ONLY (file-based). Groups: (auth), (tabs).
  core/       # App-wide composition: providers, bootstrap. No feature logic.
  features/   # Self-contained feature modules (auth, certificates, trainings, posts, ai, subscription, documentScan)
  domain/     # Framework-agnostic types/models (domain/models/*). No React, no Firebase.
  shared/     # Cross-feature building blocks: components/, services/ (api, env, firebase), utils/ (colors, theme, formatDate, validation)
```

## Dependency direction (never violate)

`app` → `features` / `core` → `shared` → `domain`

- `domain` depends on nothing. Pure types only.
- `shared` may use `domain`, never `features` or `app`.
- `features` may use `shared` + `domain`, never `app` and never another feature's internals.
- `app` (routes) wires features together but holds no business logic.

## Where code goes

- New screen/route → `src/app/...` (thin: render + wire hooks, no data logic).
- New data/business logic → `src/features/<feature>/`.
- Reusable UI with no feature knowledge → `src/shared/components/`.
- A type shared across features → `src/domain/models/`.

## Imports

Use relative imports (this repo has no path aliases): `import { Colors } from '../../shared/utils/colors'`. Keep external → internal import groups separated by a blank line.
